是阻塞会导致程序出错，我应该怎么修改这部分代码呢？

您可以使用`Flux.fromIterable()`和`concatMap`来将该阻塞部分转换为非阻塞。这将让您的代码更符合响应式编程的范式。

首先，在`forEach`之前创建一个`Flux`，如下所示：

```java
Flux.fromIterable(blobs.stream().collect(Collectors.toList()))
```

然后，使用`concatMap`对每个`blobItem`执行异步操作。确保将所有阻塞调用包装在`Mono.fromCallable()`内，并使用`subscribeOn`将它们移到另一个线程。这是修改后的代码：

```java
Flux.fromIterable(blobs.stream().collect(Collectors.toList()))
    .concatMap(blobItem -> {
        Mono<Void> setTagsMono = Mono.fromCallable(() -> {
            BlobClient blobClient = containerClient.getBlobClient(blobItem.getName());
            Map<String, String> tags = new HashMap<String, String>();
            tags.put(blobSourceConfiguration.getTagKey(), blobSourceConfiguration.getReadTagValue());
            blobClient.setTags(tags);
            return null;
        }).subscribeOn(Schedulers.boundedElastic());
        return setTagsMono;
    })
    .thenMany(Flux.fromIterable(blobs))
```

I have a problem that I can't fix:

In C# Xamarin Android, I am using an external library that takes a Func<string, string> as a parameter.
and it doesn't have async overload, but in the main time, I have to run an async code inside the method I pass to the external library.

the async code is a method that shows a user a dialog and waits for his input. and it depends on the UI context.

so if I did it like this: ShowOtpDialog().Result it blocks the main UI and causes a deadlock.


    private static string? ConfigProvider(string what)
    {
        switch (what)
        {
            case "api_id": return Application.Context.Resources!.GetString(Resource.String.apiId);
            case "api_hash": return Application.Context.Resources!.GetString(Resource.String.apiHash);
            case "phone_number": return Application.Context.Resources!.GetString(Resource.String.phoneNumber);
            case "verification_code": return ShowOtpDialog().Result;
            case "first_name": return Application.Context.Resources!.GetString(Resource.String.firstName);
            case "last_name": return Application.Context.Resources!.GetString(Resource.String.lastName);
            case "password": return Application.Context.Resources!.GetString(Resource.String.password);
            default: return null;
        }
    }

To achieve this without blocking the UI, you can consider using a `TaskCompletionSource`. With this approach, you can create a `TaskCompletionSource` that you'll use to complete the task once the OTP is available. Then, call your async `ShowOtpDialog()` method asynchronously and set the result to the task completion source when done. This way, your `Func<string, string>` won't block the UI, and you'll wait for the user input in a non-blocking way.

Here's an example of how you can implement this:

```csharp
private static TaskCompletionSource<string> _otpTcs;

private static string? ConfigProvider(string what)
{
    switch (what)
    {
        case "api_id": return Application.Context.Resources!.GetString(Resource.String.apiId);
        case "api_hash": return Application.Context.Resources!.GetString(Resource.String.apiHash);
        case "phone_number": return Application.Context.Resources!.GetString(Resource.String.phoneNumber);
